==Demographics==
The population was reported as approximately 400 people in 2005<ref name="HFG"/> and 193 at the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]],<ref>{{Cite web |date=May 2023 |title=Census Bureau profile: Mineral, Washington |url=https://data.census.gov/all?q=Mineral%20CDP,%20Washington |access-date=May 10, 2024 |publisher=United States Census Bureau}}</ref> down from 202 at the [[2010 United States census|2010 census]].<ref name="Census 2010">{{cite web |title=Total Population: 2010 Census DEC Summary File 1 (P1), Mineral CDP, Washington |url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?g=1600000US5346090&tid=DECENNIALSF12010.P1 |access-date=March 4, 2021 |website=data.census.gov |publisher=United States Census Bureau}}</ref>

